    <h2 class="accordion-header" id="panelsStayOpen-headingThree">
      <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#panelsStayOpen-collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="panelsStayOpen-collapseThree">
        HOW TO SHOP AT AUKSJONEN.NO
      </button>
    </h2>
    <div id="panelsStayOpen-collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="panelsStayOpen-headingThree">
      <div class="accordion-body">
    <div class="doc-content ng-scope"> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">1. Register</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Select "Register" and fill out the registration form to create an account. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You first choose whether you are an individual or a company, then you are asked to fill in your name, address, telephone, etc. In the field username, enter the e-mail address you want to use on auksjonen.no. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">This will then be your username. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">The username will not be visible to other users. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Then create a password of at least 6 characters. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Make sure that the form is filled in correctly. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Accounts where false information is discovered will be blocked, and suspicion of identity theft will be reported to the police. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Check if you want to receive information from Auksjonen.no via e-mail. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Press the "confirm" button at the very bottom of the page. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Then you come to a new page where you have to enter a code that you receive via SMS. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">After entering the code you received in the SMS and pressing confirm, </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">then you will receive a confirmation email. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You are now registered and your account is activated.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">2. Log in</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">When you log in to the pages of Auksjonen.no, you must enter the username (your e-mail address) and the password you chose when you registered. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Then click log in to enter the pages. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you have forgotten your password, enter your e-mail address in the username field and press "Send Password".</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">3. Your account</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Under "My Account" you will find your account information, your purchases and bids, as well as auction notifications. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You can also change the password there.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">4. Use of search engine</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Enter the keyword in the box under "search". </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">For example, you can search by: make / model, and type.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">5. Auctions</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you see an auction object that you are interested in, click on the image / link and get more information. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You are now in a detailed view of the object, and can read more about the object, see more pictures, see any condition report and / or certification, and place a bid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You will see the auction's remaining time, the item's minimum price, bid increase and minimum current bid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you want to place a bid, log in with your e-mail address and password, and click "Bid".</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">6. Outbid</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If someone makes a higher bid than yours, you will be informed of this via e-mail or SMS if desired. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You can then place a new bid if you wish.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">7. Auction monitor</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Click "Your Bids" when logged in to "My Account." </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Here you can see which auctions you are the bid leader in, if you are outbid and if you are the bid winner.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">8. You have won</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you are the bid leader at the end of the auction, you have won the bidding round. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You will receive an email from us confirming this. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Within 2 days you will receive a purchase contract with payment information etc.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">9. The course of the auction</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">During and after the auction, you will be informed by e-mail if someone places a higher bid than you, or if you get the contract for the object. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you respond to someone immediately bidding on you, this is due to the "AutoBud" feature. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Someone may have submitted an AutoBud which means that your bid has been outbid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">NB: A bid is binding and cannot be changed. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Inside the detailed view of an object you will find the full bid history. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All bids are identified by the bidder's customer number.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">10. Basic guidelines</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All auctions have a minimum price. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All bids placed after the start of the auction must be higher than or equal to the given starting bid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All auctions have a start date and an end date. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Bidding is only allowed during this time. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">In all auctions, the bids are ranked according to the size of the bid amount and the time of bidding. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All auctions have a defined bid increase (bid increment). </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">The size of the bid placed must always be the minimum bid increment larger than the bid bid above. </font></font><u><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">All bids are legally binding!</font></font></u></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">11. Autobud</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You can also place an Autobid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">The Autobud functionality registers the highest amount you want to give for the object. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Autobud will act as a bidding agent for you. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">When using autobid, the system will automatically place bids for you with the smallest bid increase until your autobid is reached. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If your auto bid cannot exceed the highest bid plus the minimum bid increase, NO bid will be placed for you. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If another user places a bid larger than your auto bid minus the minimum bid increase, your auto bid will NOT overbid this. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You can change your auto bid by entering a new desired amount in the auto bid field. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Auto bids must be set to the minimum bid plus the minimum allowable bid increase. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">An autobid cannot be deleted.</font></font></p> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If you want to change your bidding / add a bidding in an auction where you are the bidder, you must change the size of the bid in the field "Your bid" to your original bid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">If not, you will outbid your own leader bid with the current bid increase for the selected product.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">12. "Buy now" function</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Our buy now function means that you can buy the item immediately by using the buy now button. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You can also place a bid below the buy now price, then the seller has 24 hours to accept or reject your bid. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Remember that others can use the buy now function in the meantime, and that they will then get the item you are interested in.</font></font></p> <h4><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">13. Reliability bidding</font></font></h4> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">As a bidder at Auksjonen.no, you should always feel confident that the bidding is going well. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Read more about this under Safe bidding. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Unfortunately, it may happen that your internet connection or computer / tablet / mobile phone loses contact with our server, then you may miss an update on new bids. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">You will receive an e-mail that you have been outbid if you are the bidder. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">We would therefore recommend updating the website on a regular basis by "refreshing" the page.</font></font></p> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">We work consciously to keep the auction reliable and reliable at all times. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">But unfortunately technical problems can occur, this can prevent auctions from being carried out as expected. </font><font style="vertical-align: inherit;">Should this happen against all odds, we reserve the right to cancel a closed auction even if the bidder has been notified that he has the highest bid after the auction has ended (ref 6.7 and 6.12), without this entailing responsibility for Auksjonen.no.</font></font></p> <p><font style="vertical-align: inherit;"><font style="vertical-align: inherit;" class="">If you experience problems with the auction solution, contact us at technical@auksjonen.no</font></font></p> </div>
    </div>
